Program: The Documentary
Title: World Book Cafe: Beirut
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csxgn9
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 9 Jun 2018
Storytelling is a revered and longstanding tradition in Lebanese culture which is kept alive in the bustling cafes and bookshops of Beirut. Rami Ruhayem meets with a panel of poets and writers to talk about their stories; from the plight of Syrian refugees, to being an Arab who writes in English, to the rise of LGBTQ storytelling nights. Find out what itâ€™s like to be a writer in this schizophrenic mix of tradition and liberalism. (Photo: World Book Cafe panel) Show less